      "text": "Furthermore, systems theory in its Luhmannian version is blind to the growth and innovation constraints of the monetary economy. Luhmann sees that exchange has been an unintended side-effect of the institutionalization of property, but how wealth enters the world, as a kind of unintended side-effect of money, remains opaque to him. "
